  • Method Details

    • deterministic

      @OverridingEncouraged default boolean deterministic()
      Returns true if and only if this DeterministicSupplier is deterministic.

      A DeterministicSupplier is deterministic if and only if:

      • Any two invocations of the get() method return objects that are indistinguishable from one another, or
      • Any two invocations of the get() method throw RuntimeExceptions that are indistinguishable from one another

      The default implementation of this method returns false.

      Returns:
      true if and only if this DeterministicSupplier is deterministic
      See Also:
      • Supplier.get()
      Idempotency:
      This method and its overrides must be idempotent and deterministic.
      Thread Safety:
      This method is, and its overrides must be, safe for concurrent use by multiple threads.
